{% comment %}
  snippets/promo-block.liquid
  [1.2.1 → 1.1] Adapter — routes a single block to its renderer.

  Receives one block object from collection-promo.liquid and delegates
  to the correct block-type snippet. Owns no markup itself.

  Parameters:
    block  {Object}  required — a single Shopify section block

  Block types handled:
    "banner-image"        → banner-image.liquid
    "product-carousel"    → product-carousel.liquid
    "collection-carousel" → collection-carousel.liquid

  Pitfall — unknown block types:
    If a new block type is added to the schema but not handled here,
    it silently renders nothing. Add a new `when` branch here and a
    matching snippet when extending.
{% endcomment %}

{%- case block.type -%}
  {%- when 'banner-image' -%}
    {%- render 'banner-image', block: block -%}
  {%- when 'product-carousel' -%}
    {%- render 'product-carousel', block: block -%}
  {%- when 'collection-carousel' -%}
    {%- render 'collection-carousel', block: block -%}
{%- endcase -%}
